"{\"uid\": \"dailypost.ng-2024-02-28-2024-olympic-qualifier-south-africa-set-up-final-round-clash-with-super-falcons\", \"text\": \"Published  on  By  African champions South Africa and perennial rivals, Super Falcons of Nigeria, will clash in the final round of the qualifiers for the 2024 Olympic Games.  The Banyana Banyana booked a date with the Super Falcons following a 1-0 victory over Tanzania on Tuesday.  Thembi Kgatlana scored the decisive goal two minutes before the hour mark.  South Africa won the tie 4-0 on aggregate.  Nigeria won their fixture against the Indomitable Lionesses 1-0 on aggregate.  The final round tie will be staged on a home and away basis in April.  FA Cup: Erling Haaland makes history after scoring five goals for Man City  Aiyegbeni, Olofinjana to mentor NPFL youth league players  UCL: South Africa's Bartlett blames Galatasaray's 4-0 defeat to Liverpool on Osimhen's injury  South Africa: Ndah still awaiting work permit to debut for Stellenbosch FC  Nigeria, South Africa strengthen military ties to tackle terrorism, modern threats  2026 WAFCON: 'It would not happen for other tournaments' - Super Falcons' Plumptre slams CAF  WAFCON 2026: Super Falcons Ajibade disappointed with postponement  WAFCON 2026: Super Falcons decamped after postponement  Copyright \\u00a9Daily Post Media Ltd\"}"